<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900702-0166</DOCNO><DOCID>900702-0166.</DOCID><HL>   Foothill Group Says   It Will Report a Loss   For Second Quarter</HL><DATE>07/02/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   FGI</CO><IN>CDS, INTEREST RATES, COMMERCIAL PAPER (FIN)BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)</IN><LP>   LOS ANGELES -- Foothill Group said it plans to write downcertain junk bonds in its portfolio, which will lead to anestimated second-quarter net loss of between $3.8 million and$4.3 million.   The commercial lending and equipment leasing concern saidthe pretax writedowns are $6 million at Foothill Thrift andamp;Loan and $3 million at the parent Foothill Group. After tax,the write-downs will total about $5.4 million.</LP><TEXT>   A year ago, Foothill reported second-quarter net income of$3.2 million, or 32 cents a share.   Henry Jordan, chief financial officer, said Foothill'sbook value after the adjustments would be about $6.50 at June30, and the company's junk-bond securities portfolio would beless than 5% of consolidated assets. Mr. Jordan said theportfolio writedowns are unrelated to Foothill's managementof about $130 million in distressed securities in two privatelimited partnerships.   In response to the announcement, Fitch Investors Serviceaffirmed Foothill Capital Corp.'s F-2 commercial paper,noting that the financing unit has no high-yield bondportfolio and is unaffected by the writedowns.</TEXT></DOC>